      <note class="- topic/note ">The steps are only performed on the unit that should be isolated/restarted.</note>
      <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">This only isolates the unit cabinet. The other
unit and any <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">bypass or </ph>distribution cabinet
are still energized!</note>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Isolate One Unit</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To isolate
one unit in a redundant system:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the complete system operates correctly in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                        <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> and that no alarm is active.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems with individual
batteries: </b>Open the battery breaker to disconnect the battery
bank.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at
the same time for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the battery breaker to disconnect the battery
bank.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains breaker to turn
off the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch to disconnect
the DC power supply.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Discharge the DC capacitor by keeping the charging/discharge
switch in position 1 (discharge) until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the bypass isolation switch to isolate
the unit from the bypass power supply.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">output isolation switch</ph>
                        <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier output switch</ph> to isolate the unit
from the system output.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>The unit is isolated from the power supplies and the other unit.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Reconnect One Isolated Unit</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To reconnect one isolated unit in a redundant system:<note platform="WxW" type="important" class="- topic/note ">The DC capacitors needs to be charged
before the inverter input switch is closed.</note>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Close the bypass isolation switch to reconnect
the unit to the bypass power supply.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains breaker to turn
on the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
                     <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                           class="- topic/note "/>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input
power is available.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. Alternatively, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                     <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                           class="- topic/note "/>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second on the front panel.
After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>
                        <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the
DC voltage.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems
with individual batteries: </b>If the DC voltage is within tolerance,
close the battery breaker.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">The units are all running in normal operation (individually).</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">The bypass mains and static switch EN are available for all
units and within tolerance (check status on the mimic diagram).</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">No alarms are pending.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> to static bypass
operation:<ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-bypass"
                            class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li "/>
                        </ol>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Follow the same procedure and switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> to bypass operation.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both
units</u> show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the external load connection
is closed.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Close the output isolation switch to reconnect
the unit to the system output.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> to normal operation:<ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-normal"
                            class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li "/>
                        </ol>
                     </p>
                     <note class="- topic/note ">The load will be supplied by the bypass until all units
in the system have been switched back to normal operation.</note>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Follow the same procedure and switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> to normal operation.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier output switch to reconnect
the unit to the system output.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both units</u> show <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>
                        <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>The unit is reconnected to the other unit. The system is working
in parallel in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
               <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> with redundancy at the output.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
